# The Bridge Hub — project rules

This workspace is **The Bridge Hub** (`~/bridge-hub`), not the Caroline Pipeline (`~/pipeline`).

## Before building anything

1. Read [docs/README.md](docs/README.md) for orientation.
2. Use [specs/cursor-guide/FILE_OVERVIEW.md](specs/cursor-guide/FILE_OVERVIEW.md) to find the authoritative spec for your task.
3. Locked decisions in `specs/cursor-guide/` are final — do not second-guess without explicit approval from Caroline.

## Non-negotiable architecture

- Next.js 14 App Router monolith on Vercel. No separate backend repo.
- Supabase EU region. Magic link auth. No passwords.
- Scoring, AI (OpenRouter), and PDF generation run **server-side only**.
- `safety_flags` table: service role access only. Never exposed to client APIs, PDF, or email.
- PDF generates on **booking confirmation (S8) only** — never before.
- Assessment is **forward-only** — no back button. Auto-save every answer.

## Non-negotiable copy

- Disclaimer on every screen: "This is a screening tool, not a clinical diagnosis."
- No clinical labels or diagnostic language in client-facing text.
- Client report Layer 2: `specs/chat-05/chat-05-layer2-user-facing-v1.md` only.
- Therapist Layer 2: `specs/chat-03/chat-03-layer2-content-library-v2.md` only. Never mix.

## Code style

Solo builder project. Prefer clear, readable code over clever abstractions. Match existing conventions when code exists; follow specs when starting new modules.

## New session

Run the **bridge-hub-onboard** skill unless you already have full context from the current conversation.
